OL,3,CFree sea safety sessions for Channel
OL,4,CIsland youngsters
OL,6,FFree swimming sessions are teaching
OL,7,Fchildren in the Channel Islands how to
OL,8,Fswim safely in the sea.
OL,10,FAll Year 5 pupils in Jersey and
OL,11,FGuernsey are being offered the outdoor
OL,12,Fsessions as part of the Swim Safe
OL,13,Fcampaign.
OL,15,FSwim Safe is a national campaign run
OL,16,Fpartly by Swim England and the RNLI.
OL,18,FIt aims to teach young people how to
OL,19,Fstay safe in and around open water, be
OL,20,Fwary of the dangers of sea swimming,
OL,21,Fand how to enjoy swimming outdoors.
